"Kovács Z., Kakucs O., Lakó J., Rédey Á., Fülöp T., Yuzhakova T., Utasi A., Domokos E.","Environmentally friendly industrial technologies; case studies",2009,"Environmental Engineering and Management Journal","8","5",,"1003","1008",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77956964010&partnerID=40&md5=49b73249584fa449b85340ba7c835854","University of Pannonia, 10 Egyetem Str., 8200, Veszprém, Hungary; Nitrogen Works Share Co, 14 Hõsõk Sor, 8105, Pétfurdo, Hungary","Kovács, Z., University of Pannonia, 10 Egyetem Str., 8200, Veszprém, Hungary; Kakucs, O., University of Pannonia, 10 Egyetem Str., 8200, Veszprém, Hungary; Lakó, J., University of Pannonia, 10 Egyetem Str., 8200, Veszprém, Hungary; Rédey, Á., University of Pannonia, 10 Egyetem Str., 8200, Veszprém, Hungary; Fülöp, T., Nitrogen Works Share Co, 14 Hõsõk Sor, 8105, Pétfurdo, Hungary; Yuzhakova, T., University of Pannonia, 10 Egyetem Str., 8200, Veszprém, Hungary; Utasi, A., University of Pannonia, 10 Egyetem Str., 8200, Veszprém, Hungary; Domokos, E., University of Pannonia, 10 Egyetem Str., 8200, Veszprém, Hungary","Nowadays the global climate change is one of the most significant questions from environmental, social, political and economic point of views. Global warming caused by green house gases emitted into the air is a result of the human activities (Energy Revolution, 2005-2007). The majority of the industrial processes has significant impact to human life and deteriorates the natural environment. In this paper different technologies (three industrial technologies) will be dealt with special focus on energy generation and reduction of CO2 and NO/NOx emission levels. A case study to be described contributes to the increased energy security and the fulfillment of the electric energy production targets in Hungary provided on renewable basis. These plants are located in Transdanubia, Hungary.","Ch4 and no/no2 emission reduction; Co2",,,,,,,"(2003) Evolution Markets LLC, 2003. Project Design Do